JSE-listed technology company Allied Electronics (Altron) has appointed Sayeeda Khan group executive of risk and compliance, effective April 1, as it elevates the risk management and compliance function to an executive committee role. “We see corporate governance, positive control posture and compliance as a critical foundation for our growth strategy,” said Altron group CEO Mteto Nyati in a statement on Monday. “I am excited to be joining Altron to further embed our risk intelligent culture and strengthen the system of governance, compliance and controls as we accelerate delivery of the One Altron Strategy,” added Khan. She holds a Bachelor of Accountancy from the University of Durban-Westville, is a qualified chartered accountant, a certified information systems auditor through the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa, a certified internal auditor through the Institute of Internal Auditors and has completed the senior management development programme at the Gordon Institute of Business Science.